Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Place pie crust in 9-inch glass pie pan or 9-inch deep-dish glass pie pan as directed on box for One-Crust Filled Pie. In medium bowl with electric mixer, beat cream cheese, granulated sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg on medium speed until smooth. Stir in ginger. Spoon and spread filling in crust-lined pan. In large bowl, mix flour and butter. Stir in brown sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 eggs until well blended. Stir in pecans. Carefully spoon mixture evenly over filling. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set and crust is golden brown. Cool 1 hour. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, about 2 hours. Store in refrigerator.